Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula met OUTA and AA over transport-related issues on Wednesday. Courtesy of #DSTV403 JOHANNESBURG - Transport Minister Fikile Mbalula says he's considering options to solve the controversial e-tolls impasse. The minister met with the Automobile Association and the Organisation Undoing Tax Abuse (Outa) on Wednesday. WATCH: Aarto bill could trigger tax revolts The two organisations have been at the forefront of fighting against e-tolling. "We listened to both stakeholders and committed to give them feedback from our engagement processes," said Mbalula. READ: Mbalula: e-Tolls decision set for August "We will no doubt engage with the information they placed at our disposal." Mbalula said in July that there is a demand on the table to scrap e-tolls. Sanral is owed around R11-billion in unpaid fees.